<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="19" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="19">
Some authors (e.g 
<bibRefCitation author="Subba Rao, NV" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B58" refString="Subba Rao, NV, 1989. Handbook Freshwater Molluscs of India. Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta, 289 pp." title="Handbook Freshwater Molluscs of India." year="1989">Subba Rao 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nesemann, H" journalOrPublisher="Malacologia" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B45" refString="Nesemann, H, Sharma, S, Sharma, G, Khanal, SN, Pradhan, B, Shah, DN, Tachamo, RD, 2007. Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga River System. Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea (in part), 1, 263 pp." title="Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga River System. Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea (in part), 1, 263 pp." year="2007">Nesemann et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) mention 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tryon" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Gabbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Gabbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a genus. However, it seems not possible to distinguish the genera of the 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Bithyniidae</taxonomicName>
by the shape of opercula (
<bibRefCitation author="Mandahl-Barth, G" journalOrPublisher="Revue de zoologie et de botanique africaines" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="129 - 159" refId="B34" refString="Mandahl-Barth, G, 1968. Revision of the African Bithyniidae (Gastropoda Prosobranchia). Revue de zoologie et de botanique africaines 78 (1-2): 129 - 159" title="Revision of the African Bithyniidae (Gastropoda Prosobranchia)." volume="78" year="1968">Mandahl-Barth 1968</bibRefCitation>
) and/or by shell forms, because these characters are found to be variable. On the other hand, the examined material of the family of 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Bithyniidae</taxonomicName>
can be easily separated by the characteristics of penis morphology (having a penial appendix: 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Bithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Bithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Leach 1818; or lacking a penial appendix: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gloer &amp; Pesic" authorityYear="2006" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Pseudobithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Pseudobithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
&amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
2006). In our study, we tentatively use the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tryon" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Gabbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Gabbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus for small 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Bithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Bithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with a globular shell, originating from India.
</paragraph>
